criteria.driver_alignment:
REFLECT — explicitly articulates lessons on incentives (agency problems) and capital allocation trade-offs and recommends governance responses; 
IMPLEMENT — provided quantified impacts (leverage, liquidity) that ground the reflection on capital allocation; 
EVOLVE — alternative scenarios (R&D, acquisition, dividends) informed the comparative lessons about value creation vs transfer and stakeholder trade-offs.

Discover — raised the core question of why Apple would do a buyback and framed stakeholder motives;  
Implement — computed pre/post buyback metrics and compared alternative scenarios (dividend, acquisition, debt reduction, R&D);  
Reflect — explicitly weighed trade-offs, agency risks, and recommended balancing capital allocation.
